OSSRedact app icons -- OPERATOR ACTION REQUIRED
================================================

This directory must contain the application + tray icon set BEFORE running a native build
(`npm run app:build`). The Rust shell `include_bytes!`s `32x32.png` for the tray at compile time,
so a build will FAIL LOUDLY (compile error on src/lib.rs) until at least that file is present --
that is intentional: a real installer must ship a real icon.

Required files (drop them in next to this README):

  32x32.png        -- 32x32 px, RGBA PNG. Used for the system-tray icon (and Linux window icon).
                      Keep it crisp at small size; on macOS this is treated as a template image
                      (monochrome, see `iconAsTemplate: true` in tauri.conf.json), so prefer a
                      single-color silhouette with transparency for the mac menu bar.
  128x128.png      -- 128x128 px, RGBA PNG. App icon (Linux .deb/.rpm/AppImage, general bundling).
  128x128@2x.png   -- 256x256 px, RGBA PNG. Retina variant referenced by the bundle icon list.
  icon.ico         -- Windows multi-resolution .ico (include 16/32/48/64/256). Used by the NSIS/MSI
                      installer and the Windows app/tray.
  icon.icns        -- macOS .icns (include up to 512@2x / 1024). Used by the .app / .dmg bundle.

Fastest way to generate the whole set from a single 1024x1024 source PNG
------------------------------------------------------------------------
Tauri ships a generator that emits every size/format from one square source:

    cd workbench
    npx tauri icon path/to/source-1024.png

That writes 32x32.png, 128x128.png, 128x128@2x.png, icon.ico, icon.icns (and the mobile/Windows
Store sizes) straight into src-tauri/icons/. Re-run it whenever the brand mark changes.

Brand note: use the OSSRedact mark (teal shield). The tray icon should read at 16-32 px -- avoid fine
detail or text. Provide a monochrome/template-friendly silhouette so the macOS menu-bar variant looks
native in both light and dark menu bars.

These binary assets are intentionally NOT committed in this scaffold (no placeholder art shipped).
Commit the real icon set with the first real build, or keep them out of the public repo and supply
them in CI -- but they MUST exist locally for `npm run app:build` to compile.
